### PHP MySQL Introduction

MySQL is a popular database system that works well with PHP.

### Connection Methods

| Extension | Status | Description |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| `mysqli` | Active | MySQL-specific, procedural and OOP |
| `PDO` | Active | Database-agnostic, supports 12+ databases |

### MySQLi Example

```php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$dbname = "test_db";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
echo "Connected successfully";
?>
```

### Basic SQL Operations

```php
<?php
// SELECT
$sql = "SELECT id, name, email FROM users";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
    while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
        echo $row["name"] . " - " . $row["email"] . "<br>";
    }
}

// INSERT
$sql = "INSERT INTO users (name, email) VALUES ('John', 'john@example.com')";
if ($conn->query($sql) === true) {
    echo "New record created. ID: " . $conn->insert_id;
}

$conn->close();
?>
```

### Database Concepts

| Term | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Database | Collection of related tables |
| Table | Structured data with rows and columns |
| Row / Record | Single data entry |
| Column / Field | Data attribute |
| Primary Key | Unique identifier for each row |
| Foreign Key | Links tables together |
| Index | Speeds up data retrieval |

> **Key Point:** PDO is recommended over mysqli for new projects because it supports multiple database types and prepared statements with named parameters.
